edu.columbia.cs.sdarts.common
Class LSPResults

java.lang.Object
  |

        +--edu.columbia.cs.sdarts.common.LSPResults
public class LSPResults
extends LSPObject

Represents the "sqresults" header, as defined in STARTS 1.0. This object is generated by the BackEndLSP, and returned as a respone to a query from the FrontEndLSP.

An LSPResults contains the following elements:

  • The actual filter used in the query (LSPFilter)
  • The actual ranking used in the query (LSPRanking)
  • The name of the BackEndLSP where these results are coming from (LSPSource)
  • The documents in the response (LSPDoc)
If the collection supports the ranking and filter that were requested in the incoming query, the back end developer can simply pass these same objects into the LSPResults constructor. However, if only a subset is supported, the developer must instantiate new filters and rankings representing what actually was used, and pass them in. See the QueryProcessor and StandardQueryProcessor for structures that help in doing this.

The interface is designed so that the LSPResults is instantiated with the filter, ranking, and source. Documents can be added to it incrementally using the addDoc() method.

There are accessor methods for finding out what is in the results but in general these are not used. Usually, the framework will just call the toXML() method since that is the only way the framework reads the results.
